Class TwoThreeFourTree<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>

java.lang.Object
TwoThreeFourTree<E>
All Implemented Interfaces:
SearchTree<E>
public class TwoThreeFourTree<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements SearchTree<E>
An implementation of the 2-3-4 tree. A 2-3-4 tree is a search tree in which each node contains either one, two, or three data items and (other than leaves) two, three or four children. The tree is always balanced in that all leaves are on the same level, i.e., the length of the path from the root to a leaf is constant. This data structure is a special case of the B-tree, and is the basis for the Red-Black tree.
